gomodel:SYNGO_5021  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 6: Western blots of biochemical fractions from rat brain homogenate showed syntaxin-16B (STX16) was enriched in synaptic vesicle fractions obtained from A) sucrose density gradient followed by CPG column chromatography and B) clathrin coated vesicles enriched using Ficoll density gradient.\n\nBased on the known transmembrane topology of this protein, \"integral component of ... membrane\" term was selected.. Experimental description: M&M:\n\"Small synaptic vesicles were isolated from rat brain as described (Huttner et al., 1983). Clathrin-coated vesicles were purified from rat brain synaptosomes (Maycox et al., 1992).\"\n\n\"Primer construction for the amplification of rat syntaxin 16B was based on the sequences of human syntaxin 16B, a rat ESTand two mouse ESTs (GeneBank AF008936, AW524540, AI426461, and AI956297)\"\n\nWe used protein BLAST to confirm the selected rat STX16 protein sequence (uniprot accession) indeed represents syntaxin-16B targeted in the annotated paper" , "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0030285 replaced by GO:0030672" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_5021" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

